  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNDP Sudan CHF, 2014-2018</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The humanitarian situation in Sudan is still extremely critical. Around 6.6 million people are in need of humanitarian aid and two thirds of these people are located in Darfur. 

Approximately 600.000 refugees from Sudan are staying in the neighbouring countries Chad, Ethiopia and South Sudan. The UN&#xBF;s collective appeal for Sudan is USD 995 million in 2014, and it is so far financed by 54 percent. The appeal is not expected to be reduced in 2015. 

In 2012 and 2013 Denmark contributed to the UN&apos;s humanitarian country fund (CHF) for Sudan with DKK 20 million yearly, and in 2014 Denmark has so far contributed with additional DKK 10 million. The fund is a central instrument in the UN&#xBF;s capacity to offer prioritised and focused humanitarian aid through UN-organisations as well as through international NGO&apos;s.</narrative>
  </description>
